title: Two Intel rivals positioned to dominate the chip industry, report says
description: Intel is facing a "changing of the guard" in the chip industry as two competitors steal a page for its playbook, according to an analysis published by Bloomberg last week.  After Intel Corp. (Nasdaq: INTC) reported earnings reflecting an "astonishingly bad" performance, two rivals, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (NYSE: TSM) and Samsung have proved themselves as better positioned to weather a current demand downturn.  TSMC in particular "has caught and passed Intel quicker than even the most optimistic analysts had predicted," the according to the report.
